    <p>
      This is a basic Sinatra app that fetches the current open pull-requests for PuppetLabs. We require GitHub OAuth to avoid hitting rate-limits.
    </p>
    <p>
    You will see in the OAuth page we only request access to public_repos, so none of your private data will be used.
    </p>
    <p>
    PR's listed use the following query:
    <h4>user:puppetlabs is:pr is:open created:>2014-01-01</h4>
    </p>
    <a class="button" href="/auth">
      Login from GitHub
      <img class="button-github" src="/images/GitHub-Mark-32px.png">
    </a>
  </div>
</div>

